 of subhalos in redshift-space as a function of the accretion redshift 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:xi_mu"

\end_inset

 shows the 2D correlation functions split at 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}=0.5$
\end_inset

 in redshift-space for various 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

-bins: 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu=0.0-0.2$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $0.4-0.6$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $0.8-1.0$
\end_inset

.
 Different colors correspond to different 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

-bins as given in legend.
 Solid lines are 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi_{s}(s,\mu)$
\end_inset

 for the subhalos with 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}<0.5$
\end_inset

, while the dashed lines are for the subhalos with 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}>0.5$
\end_inset

.
 For small 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

-bins, the correlation functions exhibit quite different clustering at 
\begin_inset Formula $s<1h^{-1}{\rm Mpc}$
\end_inset

.
 The amplitude of correlation functions for 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}>0.5$
\end_inset

 is almost twice as large as the one for 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{{\rm acc}}<0.5$
\end_inset

.
 For large 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

-bins, the similar trend holds at 
\begin_inset Formula $s<5h^{-1}{\rm Mpc}$
\end_inset

.
 
\color black
Since these are pronounced effects, we conclude that the segregation in
 redshift-space can be measured in observations.
 
\end_layout

