reference "fig:subhaloMassFn"

\end_inset

 shows unevolved and evolved subhalo mass functions for high/low-concentration
 host halos.
 Note that the unevolved subhalo mass function implies that we use the subhalo
 mass at accretion, while we use the subhalo mass at present time for the
 evolved subhalo mass function.
 Both subhalo mass functions indicate that the subhalo mass functions for
 high-concentration halos have fewer subhalos for 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{{\rm acc}}/M_{{\rm vir}}>10^{-1.5}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{{\rm acc}}$
\end_inset

 is the subhalo mass at accretion and 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{{\rm vir}}$
\end_inset

 is the host halo mass at present.
\end_layout

